abstract: The European Union and its lending arm, the European Investment Bank, have signed deals with Bosnia worth 68 million euros (£58.42 million) to help improve the Balkan country's water supply, flood protection and transport infrastructure.
snippet: The European Union and its lending arm, the European Investment Bank, have signed deals with Bosnia worth 68 million euros (£58.42 million) to help improve the Balkan country's water supply, flood protection and transport infrastructure.
lead_paragraph: SARAJEVO — The European Union and its lending arm, the European Investment Bank, have signed deals with Bosnia worth 68 million euros (£58.42 million) to help improve the Balkan country's water supply, flood protection and transport infrastructure.
headline_main: EU and Its Lending Arm Sign $75 Million of Infrastructure Deals With Bosnia
headline_print_headline: EU and Its Lending Arm Sign $75 Million of Infrastructure Deals With Bosnia

abstract: The former official in Suffolk County was found guilty of conspiracy after a trial that exposed a culture of corruption.
snippet: The former official in Suffolk County was found guilty of conspiracy after a trial that exposed a culture of corruption.
lead_paragraph: CENTRAL ISLIP, N.Y. — He was one of the most powerful men on Long Island, serving as the top prosecutor in a suburban county with 1.5 million people. He won election after election for 15 years with bipartisan support.

abstract: The comedian, whose Netflix special “Asian Comedian Destroys America!” debuts today, shares a joke exclusively with T.
snippet: The comedian, whose Netflix special “Asian Comedian Destroys America!” debuts today, shares a joke exclusively with T.
lead_paragraph: Like much of his comedy, Ronny Chieng’s contribution to our video series “Tell T a Joke” highlights the absurdities of American culture with the prickliness of an immigrant and the timeliness of a news junkie. Born in Malaysia, and raised between New Hampshire and Singapore, the New York-based comedian embodies the perspective of the perpetual outsider peering anxiously through the looking glass. Instead of encouraging him to assimilate, Chieng says, his international upbringing only prompted him to become more himself — stereotypes of Asian submission be damned. “As a grumpy person,” he says, “when someone says that people of your race are not supposed to be grumpy, it just makes me grumpier.”

abstract: In an irate, six-page letter to Speaker Nancy Pelosi, President Trump denounced the impeachment inquiry in scathing terms, asserting that he had done nothing wrong and that Democrats would pay a political price in 2020.
snippet: In an irate, six-page letter to Speaker Nancy Pelosi, President Trump denounced the impeachment inquiry in scathing terms, asserting that he had done nothing wrong and that Democrats would pay a political price in 2020.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump on Tuesday angrily denounced the looming House votes to impeach him as a “Star Chamber of partisan persecution” by Democrats, describing the effort to remove him from office as an “attempted coup” that would come back to haunt them at the ballot box next year.

abstract: British lawmakers re-elected Labour's Lindsay Hoyle as Speaker on Tuesday, as he vowed to be impartial and fair in a moderating role which saw his predecessor John Bercow accused of breaking convention to help opponents of Brexit.
snippet: British lawmakers re-elected Labour's Lindsay Hoyle as Speaker on Tuesday, as he vowed to be impartial and fair in a moderating role which saw his predecessor John Bercow accused of breaking convention to help opponents of Brexit.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — British lawmakers re-elected Labour's Lindsay Hoyle as Speaker on Tuesday, as he vowed to be impartial and fair in a moderating role which saw his predecessor John Bercow accused of breaking convention to help opponents of Brexit.
headline_main: UK Parliament Speaker Hoyle Re-elected With Vow to Be Impartial and Fair
headline_print_headline: UK Parliament Speaker Hoyle Re-elected With Vow to Be Impartial and Fair

abstract: If you’re hearing others through the filter of your own concerns, you’re not really hearing them.
snippet: If you’re hearing others through the filter of your own concerns, you’re not really hearing them.
lead_paragraph: Ernest Hemingway put it bluntly: “Most people never listen.”

abstract: U.S. Senate Republican leader Mitch McConnell on Tuesday appeared to reject a request from the Senate's top Democrat to call new witnesses in the expected impeachment trial of President Donald Trump.
snippet: U.S. Senate Republican leader Mitch McConnell on Tuesday appeared to reject a request from the Senate's top Democrat to call new witnesses in the expected impeachment trial of President Donald Trump.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. Senate Republican leader Mitch McConnell on Tuesday appeared to reject a request from the Senate's top Democrat to call new witnesses in the expected impeachment trial of President Donald Trump.
headline_main: McConnell Suggests Senate Will Not Call Witnesses Requested by Democrats in Impeachment Trial
headline_print_headline: McConnell Suggests Senate Will Not Call Witnesses Requested by Democrats in Impeachment Trial

abstract: Negotiators reached a tentative deal to end a labor dispute that threatened this week's Democratic debate, allowing the event bringing together seven top presidential candidates to proceed, a service workers union and Democratic officials said on Tuesday.
snippet: Negotiators reached a tentative deal to end a labor dispute that threatened this week's Democratic debate, allowing the event bringing together seven top presidential candidates to proceed, a service workers union and Democratic officials said on ...
lead_paragraph: INGLEWOOD, Calif. — Negotiators reached a tentative deal to end a labor dispute that threatened this week's Democratic debate, allowing the event bringing together seven top presidential candidates to proceed, a service workers union and Democratic officials said on Tuesday.
headline_main: U.S. Democratic Debate to Proceed After Labor Dispute Settled
headline_print_headline: U.S. Democratic Debate to Proceed After Labor Dispute Settled

abstract: The trial opens on Thursday of a businessman and three others charged over the murder of an investigative journalist and his fiancee in what is seen as a test of Slovakia's judicial and political system ahead of an election in February.
snippet: The trial opens on Thursday of a businessman and three others charged over the murder of an investigative journalist and his fiancee in what is seen as a test of Slovakia's judicial and political system ahead of an election in February.
lead_paragraph: BRATISLAVA — The trial opens on Thursday of a businessman and three others charged over the murder of an investigative journalist and his fiancee in what is seen as a test of Slovakia's judicial and political system ahead of an election in February.
headline_main: Trial Over Slovak Journalist's Murder Puts Justice System to Test
headline_print_headline: Trial Over Slovak Journalist's Murder Puts Justice System to Test
